# Project standards

Monorepo: `packages/react` (`@nerdfish/react`), `apps/docs`, `packages/utils` (`@nerdfish/utils`).

## Stack

- **Components**: `@nerdfish/react` — built on `@base-ui/react`, styled with Tailwind v4
- **Utilities**: `cn`, `cva` from `@nerdfish/utils/class`
- **Styles**: `@nerdfish/react/styles/global.css` — semantic tokens, not generic Tailwind/shadcn aliases
- **Docs**: `apps/docs` — MDX pages with live examples importing `@nerdfish/react/*`

Compose from existing `@nerdfish/react` primitives (`button`, `dialog`, `item`, `field`, etc.) before adding new ones.

## Code style

- Functional components with `function` keyword; no classes
- Named exports; lowercase-dash directories (`components/attachment`)
- Prefer interfaces over types; avoid enums — use maps
- Concise, declarative TypeScript; descriptive names (`isLoading`, `hasError`)
- File order: types → variants → component → subcomponents

## React & Next.js

- Favor Server Components; minimize `'use client'`, `useEffect`, `setState`
- `'use client'` only for Web APIs or interactive leaf components
- Wrap client components in `Suspense` with fallback
- Use Zod for input validation; `next-safe-action` for server actions
- Optimize Web Vitals (LCP, CLS, INP)

## UI

- Use semantic spacing/color/radius tokens — see `design-tokens.mdc`
- Mobile-first responsive design
- Import components: `import { Button } from '@nerdfish/react/button'`
